children.subject: I don’t think 61c and 186 is a bad combo. 186 project is more 61b style while 152 might rely on more 61c knowledge.

history.content:
Taking 152 concurrently with 61C is like taking 170 concurrent with 61B/70, it's not a good idea. In fact, 152 directly follows 61C as it dives deeper into the concepts of Computer Architecture covered in 61C. So don't take 152 and 61C concurrently. That's a bad combo.

61C and 186 is a perfectly doable combo. There are some concepts in 186 that are covered in 61C (memory management, I/O) but nothing too complex. 186 really only requires 61B as there is a lot of Java programming and emphasis on data structures.

Edit: Don't take 186 without 61C. You need to spend a semester understanding the basic principles of computer architecture before jumping into an application like databases. Hold your horses and don't rush into something you don't fully understand.
